---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../site.config";

const updated = "June 26, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Nile"
  description="The terms governing your use of the Nile platform."
  canonical="/terms"
>
  <section class="legal-page nile-section">
    <div class="nile-container legal-container">
      <div class="legal-header">
        <p class="nile-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body">

        <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the Nile platform, including joinnile.com and the Nile mobile application (collectively, the "Service"), operated by Nile ("we," "us," or "our"). By creating an account or using the Service, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.</p>
        <p>The Service is currently available to residents of the United States only.</p>

        <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>You must be at least 13 years old to use the Service. By using the Service, you represent that you meet this requirement. If you are under 18, you represent that a parent or legal guardian has reviewed and agreed to these Terms on your behalf.</p>

        <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activity that occurs under your account. You must provide accurate information when creating your account and keep it up to date. Notify us immediately via our <a href="/contact">contact page</a> if you suspect unauthorized access to your account.</p>
        <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms or that have been inactive for an extended period.</p>

        <h2>3. The Platform — Hosts and Viewers</h2>

        <h3>All events on Nile are ticketed</h3>
        <p>Nile is a platform for ticketed live events and on-demand replays. All events require a ticket purchase; free events are not supported.</p>

        <h3>Hosts</h3>
        <p>If you create and broadcast events on Nile ("Host"), you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Only stream content you have the rights to broadcast, including any music, video, or performances</li>
          <li>Not stream content that is illegal, abusive, harassing, defamatory, or infringes any third-party intellectual property rights</li>
          <li>Honor the event details (title, description, scheduled time, duration) presented to ticket buyers</li>
          <li>Fulfill your obligations to ticket buyers — if you cancel an event, you are responsible for issuing refunds through the platform</li>
          <li>Comply with all applicable laws, including those governing performances, licensing, and taxation of income</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Hosts receive approximately 50% of net revenue after platform and payment processing costs. Exact amounts are displayed in your dashboard before and after each event. Payouts are processed via Stripe Connect and are subject to Stripe's terms and payout schedule.</p>

        <h3>Viewers</h3>
        <p>Ticket purchases are final. Refunds are only issued if a Host cancels an event or if we determine a technical failure on our side prevented you from accessing the event. If you believe you are entitled to a refund, <a href="/contact">contact us here</a>.</p>
        <p>Live ticket buyers receive free access to the on-demand replay of that event. Viewers who did not purchase a live ticket may purchase VOD access separately.</p>

        <h2>4. Prohibited Conduct</h2>
        <p>You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose or in violation of these Terms</li>
          <li>Stream, post, or transmit content that is sexually explicit, violent, hateful, or harassing</li>
          <li>Infringe on the intellectual property rights of any person or entity</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Service or another user's account</li>
          <li>Use automated tools (bots, scrapers, crawlers) to access the Service without our written permission</li>
          <li>Interfere with or disrupt the integrity or performance of the Service</li>
          <li>Impersonate any person or misrepresent your affiliation with any entity</li>
          <li>Engage in ticket fraud, chargebacks without a valid basis, or any activity designed to manipulate our payout system</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Content You Post</h2>
        <p>You retain ownership of content you create on Nile. By posting content, you grant us a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to host, display, and distribute that content as necessary to operate the Service. This license ends when you delete the content or your account, subject to any copies made by other users (e.g., screenshots).</p>
        <p>We do not monitor all content but reserve the right to remove any content that violates these Terms or applicable law.</p>

        <h2>6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>The Nile name, logo, and all platform software are the intellectual property of Nile. Nothing in these Terms grants you a right to use our trademarks, trade names, or logos without our prior written consent.</p>

        <h2>7. Payments and Fees</h2>
        <p>All payments are processed by Stripe. By making or receiving payments through the Service, you agree to <a href="https://stripe.com/legal/ssa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe's Terms of Service</a>. We are not responsible for errors made by Stripe.</p>
        <p>We reserve the right to change our fee structure with reasonable notice. Changes will not affect events that have already been published and sold.</p>

        <h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, ERROR-FREE, OR FREE OF VIRUSES.</p>
        <p>We are not responsible for the content, quality, or legality of events hosted by third-party Hosts. Ticket purchases are transactions between you and the Host; Nile acts as a platform intermediary.</p>

        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, NILE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUE, WHETHER INCURRED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY. IN NO EVENT SHALL OUR AGGREGATE LIABILITY EXCEED THE GREATER OF $100 OR THE AMOUNT YOU PAID TO US IN THE 12 MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.</p>

        <h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Nile and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, liabilities, damages, and expenses (including attorneys' fees) arising out of your use of the Service, your content, or your violation of these Terms.</p>

        <h2>11. Termination</h2>
        <p>You may close your account at any time via Settings → Delete Account. We may suspend or terminate your access at any time, with or without notice, for conduct that violates these Terms or is harmful to other users, third parties, or the Service.</p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, without regard to its conflict-of-law provisions. Any dispute arising from these Terms or the Service shall be resolved in the state or federal courts located in Riverside County, California, and you consent to the jurisdiction of those courts.</p>

        <h2>13. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. We will notify you of material changes by email or by posting a notice in the Service at least 14 days before the changes take effect. Continued use of the Service after the effective date constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>

        <h2>14. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms? <a href="/contact">Contact us here</a>.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding-block: var(--nile-s-16);
  }
  .legal-container {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--nile-s-12);
  }
  .legal-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--nile-font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin: var(--nile-s-3) 0 var(--nile-s-3);
  }
  .updated {
    color: var(--nile-txt-tertiary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .legal-body {
    color: var(--nile-txt-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  .legal-body p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--nile-s-4);
  }
  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--nile-font-display);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--nile-txt-primary);
    margin: var(--nile-s-10) 0 var(--nile-s-3);
  }
  .legal-body h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--nile-txt-primary);
    margin: var(--nile-s-6) 0 var(--nile-s-2);
  }
  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 var(--nile-s-4);
    padding-left: var(--nile-s-6);
  }
  .legal-body li {
    margin-bottom: var(--nile-s-2);
  }
  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--nile-volt);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .legal-body a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
